<subSubSection id="C33A651A987A5A78DADCFD84D34DFBDC" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F3691987A5A78DADCFD84D00DFD75" blockId="102.[189,1399,527,661]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
This species used to be included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D12987A5A78D80FFD84D154FDC9" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[622,833,527,553]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">
<emphasis id="B954EA83987A5A78D80FFD84D154FDC9" box="[622,833,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Pipistrellus kuhlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but as found by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B60987A5A78DE78FD84D756FDCA" author="Gopfert" box="[1049,1347,527,554]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Gopfert" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="68 - 69" refId="ref262204" refString="Gopfert M. C., Heller K. G., Volleth M. &amp; Wasserthal L. T. 1995. Madagascar microchiropteran bats: new records including new species. Bat Research News 36 (4): 68 - 69." type="journal article" year="1995">
Göpfert 
<emphasis id="B954EA83987A5A78DE1FFD9BD6AEFDC9" box="[1150,1211,527,553]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
(1995: 68)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B60987A5A78DADCFDB8D3F3FDAD" author="Volleth" box="[189,486,563,589]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Volleth" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="25 - 46" refId="ref275486" refString="Volleth M., Bronner G., Gopfert M. C., Heller K. - G., von Helversen O. &amp; Yong H. - S. 2001. Karyotype comparison and phylogenetic relationships of Pipistrellus - like bats (Vespertilionidae; Chiroptera; Mammalia). Chromosome Research 9 (1): 25 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1026787515840" type="journal article" year="2001">
Volleth 
<emphasis id="B954EA83987A5A78DB7DFDBFD34FFDAD" box="[284,346,563,589]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">et al.</emphasis>
(2001: 28)
</bibRefCitation>
, the sub-Saharan specimens have a different chromosome number than the specimens from Europe and northern Africa. For these sub-Saharan populations, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B60987A5A78DE1AFDDCD758FD91" author="Kock" box="[1147,1357,599,625]" firstAuthor="Kock" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="277 - 283" refId="ref268364" refString="Kock D. 2001. Identity of the African Vespertilio hesperida Temminck 1840 (Mammalia, Chiroptera, Vespertilionidae). Senckenbergiana Biologica 81 (1 / 2): 277 - 283." type="journal article" year="2001">Kock (2001: 277)</bibRefCitation>
reinstated the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D12987A5A78DBF3FDF1D004FD74" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[402,529,634,660]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">
<emphasis id="B954EA83987A5A78DBF3FDF1D004FD74" box="[402,529,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">hesperidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F3691987A5A78DADCFD37D34DFBDC" blockId="102.[189,1399,700,1084]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
Specimens belonging to this species were collected at three localities in the CRB area: two in 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78DF77FD37D763FD36" box="[1302,1398,700,726]" name="Rwanda" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
(Mutura and Kitabi) and one in 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D83DFD6BD0A9FD1A" box="[604,700,736,762]" name="Burundi" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Burundi</collectingCountry>
(Nyamugari Hill). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B60987A5A78D9D5FD6AD6D0FD1B" author="Kearney" box="[948,1221,736,763]" firstAuthor="Kearney" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" pagination="629 - 631" refId="ref267427" refString="Kearney T. C. 2013 d. Pipistrellus hesperidus Dusk Pipistrelle. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 629 - 631. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="d">Kearney (2013d: 630)</bibRefCitation>
indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D12987A5A78DADCFC8ED349FCFE" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[189,348,772,798]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">
<emphasis id="B954EA83987A5A78DADCFC8ED349FCFE" box="[189,348,772,798]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">P. hesperidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in a narrow band in eastern Africa, reaching from southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78DF7EFC8FD767FCFE" box="[1311,1394,772,798]" name="Eritrea" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
, over western 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78DB3DFCACD3D7FCA1" box="[348,450,807,833]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D84BFCACD0D5FCA1" box="[554,704,807,833]" name="South Sudan" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D933FCACD1A5FCA1" box="[850,944,807,833]" name="Uganda" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, where it splits into two branches, one along the Kenyan-Tanzanian border reaching the coast, and a second along the great lakes to eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78DADCFCE4D32FFC69" box="[189,314,879,905]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
and the eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D867FCE4D057FC69" box="[518,578,879,905]" name="South Africa" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">RSA</collectingCountry>
, reaching just north of Port Elizabeth. Additionally, she marked the presence of the species in the Mount 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D8ECFC18D112FC4D" box="[653,775,915,941]" name="Cameroon" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
area and in 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D9C6FC18D619FC4D" box="[935,1036,915,941]" name="Djibouti" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
, with some further individual localities in northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78DB87FC3DD05CFC30" box="[486,585,950,976]" name="Somalia" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, western 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D8D9FC3DD100FC30" box="[696,789,950,976]" name="Zambia" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78D97EFC3DD160FC30" box="[799,885,950,976]" name="Angola" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Angola</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3377601987A5A78DE7AFC3CD64DFC31" box="[1051,1112,951,977]" name="South Africa" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">RSA</collectingCountry>
. Furthermore, she refers to Jakob Fahr, who indicated that some records from West Africa might be misidentified. The SDM map confirms the presence of the species in eastern Africa. The records from West Africa might need to be re-examined.
</paragraph>
